11/07/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Lawmakers approved on Friday (July 9th) a bill to hold a population census from April 1st-15th 2011. 
Representatives of the ruling parties and the opposition agreed to strengthen control of the process. 
The census is expected to cost about 3.5m euros and will be Montenegro's first since 2003. 
(Mina, Radio Free Europe, SEEbiz - 09/07/10)
